CAPE TOWN - There’s been a breakthrough in the social grants impasse.
	
	Government has announced a hybrid payment system between the SA Social Security Agency (Sassa) and the Post Office. Minister Jeff Radebe said an inter-ministerial committee will fast-track the payment system partnership. An agreement will be signed next Friday and sent to Parliament the following week. The exact details of the deal have not yet been revealed.  !function(d,s,id){var js,fjs=d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0],p=/^http:/.test(d.location)?'http':'https';if(!d.getElementById(id)){js=d.createElement(s);js.id=id;js.src=p+"://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js";fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js,fjs);}}(document,"script","twitter-wjs"); eNCA